CLASSIC BLUE:
1 3/4 oz Empress 1908 Gin
1/3 oz Giffard Pamplemousse
1/3 oz Dry Vermouth
1/3 oz @tealeavesco Classic Blue Tea
Express lemon peel

METHOD: Stir ingredients on ice. Strain into chilled a Nick & Nora glass. Express lemon peel and garnish with a grapefruit peel (or blueberries for an extra pop of Classic Blue!) #Pantone2020
Drinking age to follow. Sip responsibly.

By extending the sensory reach of PANTONE 19-4052 Classic Blue, Pantone is hoping to reach a greater diversity of people to provide everyone with an opportunity to engage with the Color of the Year 2020 in their own unique way.  Pantone partnered with @weareFirmenich, the worldâ€™s largest privately-owned fragrance company to create the essence of the â€œsmellâ€ of PANTONE 19-4052 Classic Blue. The scent of PANTONE 19-4052 Classic Blue is a fragrant contemplation of where sky and sea meet â€“ a boundless blue where there is no end. The scent first opens with notes of blue water and sea salt lifted by airy sky. An accord of a fluffy cloud combines with water lily and seaweed, with notes of blue musk, soothing minerals, and ocean timber for depth, calm and a reassuring finish. The smell of PANTONE 19-4052 Classic Blue is brought to life through a candle that will transport you into a state of contemplation and a feeling of optimism for the future.
